      <img class="photos" src="images/adanakebab.jpg">
      <div class="cooking">
        <h4>Ingredients:</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>1 lb lean ground mutton</li>
          <li>50 gr fat from lamb tail, finely chopped</li>
          <li>1 tsp crushed red pepper</li>
          <li>1/2 tsp black pepper</li>
          <li>1/2 tsp cumin</li>
          <li>1 tsp salt to taste</li>
          <li>Skewers or chop sticks</li>
        </ul>
        <h4>Preperation :</h4>
        <p>Leave the crushed red pepper in 1/2 cup of water <br>for about 2-3 hours, to get them softened. Then drain.</p>
        <p>Mix all the ingredients with your hands.<br> Grab a fist size mixture and skewer it. <br>Squeeze it on the skewer until it gets smooth and <br>lengthens to acquire the shape shown in the picture.<br> Cook on a grill or oven. You can grill<br> some vegetables as well on the side. <br>Refrigerate the skewered Adana Kebab <br>overnight to get a better flavor.</p>
